In Figure \ref{fig5a} the same graph is used to exemplify the community structure mapped by the edge-betweenness function available in RedeR. In Figure \ref{fig5b} these communities are nested to containers, which are objects of the same class of the nodes but with additional behaviors (Fig.\ref{fig5c}). You can build these containers either using \emph{R} or \emph{Java} functions (see options available in the \emph{clustering} main menu and in the shortcuts of the nested objects, i.e., right-click a container).

